# Trochilidae Knowledge Graph (TKG): Biodata Curation

[![R-Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/R-4.2+-blue.svg)](https://www.r-project.org/)
[![Institution](https://img.shields.io/badge/UNAM-National%20Autonomous%20University%20of%20Mexico-gold)](https://www.unam.mx/)
[![Dictionary-Size](https://img.shields.io/badge/Colors-641%20Curated-green.svg)](data/color_dictionary_hbw_wikidata.csv)

## Project Overview
This repository contains the computational pipeline for the **Trochilidae Knowledge Graph (TKG)**. The project integrates citizen science (iNaturalist), taxonomic authorities (IOC/GBIF), and semantic web technologies (Wikidata/RDF) to create a high-resolution phenotypic matrix of hummingbird plumage across 14 anatomical regions.

## Repository Structure
- `scripts/01_data_acquisition.R`: Automated harvesting of research-grade observations.
- `scripts/02_matrix_expansion.R`: Generation of the 14-region phenotypic matrix (47,320 data points).
- `scripts/03_tkg_visualizer.R`: A semi-automated tool to facilitate expert biocuraduría.
- `scripts/04_biocentric_dictionary.R`: Advanced filtration of Wikidata entities to establish a specialized color lexicon.

## Key Data Components
### Biocentric Color Dictionary
The TKG utilizes a curated lexicon of **641 color entities** derived from Wikidata. To ensure scientific rigor, we implemented a strict filtration protocol that:
* **Excluded** industrial standards (Pantone, RAL, ISCC).
* **Purged** non-biological "noise" (commercial brands, cellular/metabolic processes).
* **Sanitized** "ghost entities" (QID-only labels).
* **Mapped** optical properties (Iridescent vs. Pigmentary) to facilitate phenotypic modeling.

## Getting Started
1. Clone the repository.
2. Run `scripts/01_data_acquisition.R` to establish the taxonomic backbone.
3. Run `scripts/04_biocentric_dictionary.R` to generate the sanitized color mapping.
4. Use the `TKG Visualizer` to verify phenotypic traits against the HBW Color Standard using the 641-color master list.

